         <div>
            <head>Creating the macro-structure of the dictionary</head>
            <p>On oXygen, create a new document based upon the <mentioned>TEI all</mentioned> customisation.</p>
            <div>
               <head>Importance of the metadata in <gi>teiHeader</gi></head>
               <list>
                  <item>Basic description (title, author, project) of the docuement in <ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-titleStmt.html"><gi>titleStmt</gi></ref>:
                        <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <titleStmt>
                           <title>Step by step introduction to the TEI dictionary chapter</title>
                           <author>
                              <persName>
                                 <forename>Laurent</forename>
                                 <surname>Romary</surname>
                              </persName>
                           </author>
                        </titleStmt>
                     </egXML></item>
                  <item>Publication responsability and re-use options in <ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-publicationStmt.html"><gi>publicationStmt</gi></ref>:
                        <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <publicationStmt>
                           <authority>
                              <persName>
                                 <forename>Laurent</forename>
                                 <surname>Romary</surname></persName>
                           </authority>
                           <availability>
                              <licence target="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">
                                 <p>The Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported (CC BY 3.0) Licence applies to this document.</p>
                              </licence>
                           </availability>
                        </publicationStmt>
                     </egXML>
                  </item>
                  <item>Possible source(s) in <ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-sourceDesc.html"><gi>sourceDesc</gi></ref>, in the case of the present script: <egXML
                        xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <sourceDesc>
                           <p>Born digital TEI document</p>
                        </sourceDesc>
                     </egXML>
                  </item>
               </list>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Organising the dictionary as a (structured) series of entries</head>
               <p>Using the <ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-div.html"><gi>div</gi></ref> element to organise sequences of <ref
                     target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-entry.html"><gi>entry</gi></ref> elements:</p>
               <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <div type="letter" n="A">
                     <entry>...</entry>
                     <entry>...</entry>
                  </div>
               </egXML>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Implementing the word to sense lexical organisation (aka semasiological)</head>
               <p>To reflect the semasiological orentation, the two main elements of an <gi>entry</gi> are:</p>
               <list>
                  <item><ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-form.html"><gi>form</gi></ref>, which groups together all the form related information</item>
                  <item><ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-sense.html"><gi>sense</gi></ref>, which groups together all the semantic informaiton associated to the
                     form</item>
               </list>
               <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <entry xml:lang="fr">
                     <form>...</form>
                     <sense>...</sense>
                  </entry>
               </egXML>
               <p><gi>sense</gi> can be iterated and is recursive</p>
               <p>The <att>xml:lang</att> attribute can be used on <gi>entry</gi> to represent the object language. It can be used again for specific elements within <gi>entry</gi> when the working
                  language is different.</p>
               <note>The TEI Lex 0 iniitative recommends that all sense related information be embedded in a <gi>sense</gi> element and not left flat within <gi>entry</gi></note>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Component of the form</head>
               <p><gi>form</gi> may contain:</p>
               <list>
                  <item><ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-orth.html"><gi>orth</gi></ref> for the orthographic form</item>
                  <item><ref target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-pron.html"><gi>pron</gi></ref> for the pronunciation</item>
               </list>
               <p>Additional elements are available for syllabification, hyphenation, etc. Have a lokk at the members of the <ref
                     target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-model.formPart.html">model.formPart</ref> class.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Additonal grammatical information</head>
               <p>The <gi>gramGrp</gi> element can be used to provide the morphosyntactic properties of the lemma.</p>
               <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <entry>
                     <form type="lemma">...</form>
                     <gramGrp>
                        <pos>n</pos>
                        <gen>f</gen>
                     </gramGrp>
                  </entry>
               </egXML>
               <p>The main elements that can be used here are <gi>pos</gi>, <gi>gen</gi>, <gi>case</gi>, <gi>mood</gi>, <gi>number</gi>, <gi>per</gi>, <gi>tns</gi> and the generic <gi>gram</gi>
                  element together with a <att>type</att> attribute.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Sense related information</head>
               <p>Within the <gi>sense</gi> element, it is possible to gather various types of information such as usage (<gi>usg</gi>), definition (<gi>def</gi>), examples (<gi>cit</gi>) or etymology
                     (<gi>etym</gi>).</p>
               <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <entry>
                     <form>...</form>
                     <sense>
                        <usg type="">...</usg>
                        <def>...</def>
                        <cit type="example">
                           <quote/>
                           <bibl>...</bibl>
                        </cit>
                        <etym>...</etym>
                     </sense>
                  </entry>
               </egXML>
               <p>You can rely on the TEI documentation to explore the various elements and their constructs (google search: <q>tei element sense</q>): <ref
                     target="http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-sense.html"><gi>sense</gi></ref></p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Related entries</head>
               <p>The <gi>re</gi> element embeds <gi>entry</gi>-like content for describing related entries:</p>
               <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <entry>
                     <form>...</form>
                     <sense>...</sense>
                     <re>
                        <form>...</form>
                        <sense>...</sense>
                     </re>
                  </entry>
               </egXML>
               <note><gi>re</gi> can also appear in <gi>sense</gi></note>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>Final remarks</head>
            <list>
               <item>Using TEI all provides far too many elements in the schema. It is possible to create a limited customisation with a subset of TEI elements. Ask the organisers!</item>
            </list>
         </div>
